mesg "Okay - query_level version 2.0 now works...It's the same thing, but if you send it a string, it'll return thelevel of the class (OR group!) entered...For example, say \"player\" was a 10th level necromancer/4th levelfighter.player->query_level() would return the sum of the 2 classes (in thiscase, 14)player()->query_level(\"wizard\") or player->query_level(\"necromancer\")would both return 10.Etc, etc...-Cy"
